name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
It's always a relaxing to walk around Pasir Ris park; nice beach, forest, fishing ponds,wildlife etc.

Its mangrove and boardwalk built through forest provide good platform to observe and immerse in nature.

There are monitor lizards, fishes, turtles, hornbills and other birds. There are few ponds for fishing activities.

The biking track is also quite wide and playground is nice. Kids get fun experiences.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: It's a beautiful park by the beach where the breeze is so nice and the wave sounds will carm my mind and soul. Love to walk at this park. There are few nice bar and place to eat at the park. The kids playground is huge. Also, have designated place to learn roller blades. This park have volleyball court as well.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Really fun place the mangrove was quite dangerous I sunk knee deep into the mud so be careful, bring extra pair of clothing and shoes. The broad walk was interesting will surely go again. Helped clean up the area a bit also

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: A relaxing beach front park. A big long lagoon for water activities with showing facilities nearby. F&B cafe, horse ridding activities for children and a big sandy playground in the vicinity. A wonderful park for family. Love it.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
We cycled from Tampines to Pasir Ris town Park, entered fr Carpark C and cycled all along the beach til the end of the cycling track there was a connecting track to Lorong Halus but since that wasn't our plan for the day we skipped it.  Lots of trees to provide shelter from the sun in this part of the beach. We cycled back to starting point, went towards the Mangrove Boardwalk and realised we forgot our mozzie/insect repellent spray so didn't enter the boardwalk. We just cycled around the around the BBQ pits area but since there weren't enough trees there to give us shelter we headed back out.
So basically some parts of the beach has better shelter from the sun than others.
There were 3 places that you can get some snacks there but prices aren't cheap. Somehow there seem to be many chicken in the park there.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Very relaxing and cosy area to enjoy the breeze, sun and sea. There is a Bistro here called Georges @Cove with very nice ambient and view.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: 04 Apr 2022: Amazing place for the young and not so young to have fun. A wonderful experience at the beautiful mangrove forest...fantastic surroundings and getting close to the native inhabitants.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Brought my gal here for a playdate with her BFFs. She had a lot of fun and enjoyable moments trying out slides, swings and flying fox. There is this round seat that can send u to do a 360⁰ turn, exciting must try!!

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Always a wonderful experience being at this place where people can relax, play , bond , stroll and make beautiful memories. Lovely place!

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: The beach is full of rubbish (can see during low tide). There is a hornbill and it’s nest (park ranger has cordoned the area around the tree - well done). Many clusters of chicken. 😊

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
This park has been my favorite run place because it offers a very relaxing view and has a lot of other attractions.
A lot of people regularly visits the park specially on a weekend. They can camp or have a picnic, set up a chair and do fishing, watch kids happily playing in the playground, wait and observe for various species in the mangrove, and walk/run/cycle whichever they prefer.
Still always excited to go here🏃🏻‍♀️❤️

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Great park to host BBQ parties. In addition, it is a great place to have a walk while seeing the sea.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: A relax and chill beach park, palm trees and mature trees an added bonus. Views of kelongs, cargo ships and cruises out in the sea, onland there are separate cycle and pedestrians  paths (except paths are not clearly marked hence bicycles are fohnd speeding on pedestrian  path), toilet facilities and onsite restaurants. There are various car parks which on weekends & Public holidays can get awful busy.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: This park is near the beach.  Even though some parts are under construction, the park is still big enough to cater to people who likes to jog, walk or cycle. Even strolling n enjoy the scenery and sometimes catches sight of wild animals like otters or wild birds like hornbill n eagle. If u go at the right time, u may catch sunrise or sunsets.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: A very large and well maintained beach park. You can pack your lunch and have a picnic with your family and friends here. It is very Picturesque. It has two restrooms. BBQ spaces are available too. I would recommend it to be visited for a peaceful family outing.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: I always came here to enjoy my off day.nice scenery, nice beach, quite place. I love it

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Fascinated by beautiful scenery, clean campsite and I enjoyed the breeze. Safe place to exercise and outdoor activities.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Peacefull place. I spent there almost 4 course sitting watching the sea. Feeling the breeze air. It was chilled. You can book a pit there to spent some good time with family.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Beautiful and peaceful park - lots of wild chickens roaming around

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Pasir ris Park is a park and is wheelchair accessible and have food there too

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: A very open space and big park in the east side.There is also lots of nature around, such as flowers, animals, trees, and much more.One can even spotted a monitor lizard swimming happily in the water and a huge swarm of mangrove jellyfishes seen through the water. The beautiful park is mostly used for recreational activities such as walking, exercising, cycling, playing,etc. A play park that even have swings,slides and some adventurous activities for the children. Its a park for all to have their fun activities.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Very tranquil park that has a sufficient number of trees to provide ample shade. It's perfect for taking a stroll after having a meal at the nearby hawker centre. Just need to look out for the bike riders though, who sometimes go a little fast and do not ring their bells.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
Went to the newly opened Thereuputic Garden.
Slightly on the small side.
Can easily be missed if seen from the jogging and cycling path beachside.
Peaceful and quiet with a small exercise area.
The rest of the beach/ park area is as always a nice place for walking, jogging, cycling and generally soaking in the nice beach atmosphere.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
Be filled with nature, interesting wildlife such as roosters and random visiting birds. The park’s a great place for beginner inline skaters. Most parts of the roads are smooth with quite abit of fun slopes to glide about.

Especially spacious too!

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Booked a bbq pit and spent some quality time with friends and family. was abl to fly a kite after almost 15 years and felt nostalgic. overall a good experience. pit is reasonably priced and clean. lot of active crowd.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
Love the environment so peaceful .
Love it ♥️

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: I was shocked to see so much trash on the beach. This is not the image I have of Singapore. You would think you are in Malaysia. Instead of cleaning up the beach, there were 5 South Asian workers cutting the gras, which is so short that there is no need whatsoever to do so...

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Beautiful park! Ample parking space for those who need to drive here. Swimming pool just beside. Try your taste buds on local delights at the Hawker Centre nearby (huge!) or the McDonald's! 😅 The fishing pond is divided between adults and kids sections. The jogging track is puts you through a gradual up and down gradient. Suitable for any runner. Public toilets are also nearby for that urgent moment.. 😁 <<T a N>>

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: There's toilet, nearby parking lots(Hawker and CC), playground, fishing, exercise area, beside Hawker, alot of tree shades, good birdwatching location, great relaxing place. There's McDonald and Burger King in the CC.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: good park but got a lot of smokers. But can fishing. Even though i dont like fishing i think it is very cool. name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
What a park.
Jogging along the beach is the perfect thing one can do in the morning.
Good breeze while jogging and meeting like minded joggers too.
A very neat and tidy area.
You  can hire a bicycle and ride as far as your legs can carry you.
There are rest rooms for your drinks and relaxation as well.
Nice place to be anytime of the day.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: It's mostly good place for me, because there was wonderful sports place 💞💞💞.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: A place where many enjoy strolling and cycle there. It leads to Pasir Ris Hawker Centre, sports centre, Bus Interchange, White Sands mall or even to Pasir Ris Beach. For fishing lover, there is a popular fishing spot at the park or crossing the road over to Aranda Country Club, you can find a lovely place for prawning too!  Next to Aranda Country Club is Downtown East, Ehub , E'Aveune!

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Nice town park with a pond... Few eatery's around with beer garden too... Good for relaxation (recently getting so crowded so no more relax)... There a hawker centre next to it that have some goods food thou... Try it ..

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Love nature? Then this park close to the see and the nature park at Coney Island is the place to be at! Safe cycling track to bring you to Pasir Ris to the east and Notrtshore to the west!

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Nice park near the shore. The beach is really small though. There are BBQ pits in the camping area. There are big playgrounds for kids, so it is a nice place to bring the children.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Wooden walkway offers close look of the marshes, mangrove and plants. 4 storey high tower did not offer panaromic view of park as there were many tall trees surrounding it. Saw many avid photographers taking pictures.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
Fantastic place,  inconvenience for Elders  to come here.  From car parking to reach here If park management arrange wheel chair for them are very Convenient for them  (at-least for week ends ).
it’s like my Home . I was spend all time here. whenever get free times. really awesome No words well maintain Pasir Ris Park council Hats off.
.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Nice and quiet with a lot of beautiful old trees and popular spot for bird photography enthusiasts. A nice green place in our little red dot.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Very nice place to spend time with your family and kids. There is a waterbody if you want to watch fishing or try your luck in the fishing. There is a playground for kids and I am sure they love it. Ample of space to play other games like soft cricket, badminton, and light football just for fun. No formal area to play those, but just like grabbing and start playing. If you feel hungry then food court is available within the park premises, so that should not be a problem. I think the park has all that you need to be with the nature and spend time in the evening. Lots of trees, shelter and walk in the nature.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Very scenic quiet town park with a fishing pond for avid anglers. U will enjoy a walk or jog anytime of the day.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Great Park... the mangrove section with its board walk was simply awesome... water sports - kayaking was busy... Nice, serene walk... kudos to NParks!

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Super loved this place! Because I always love the park plus the sea! Very wide area for biking, for running or maybe for a picnic. And oh! I saw some of them had a place for an  overnight camp! I also loved to watch the wild birds flying around the area.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Probably a good example of a creatively designed tennis court. Although it is a little flawed - tennis balls gets stuck way too high on the fence and dried leaves needs constant maintenance along the floor area. Other facilities of pretty neat too. Overall quite a compact sports center

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Tranquil, not crowded. The area is clean and constantly improving in terms of facilities, i.e. toilets,  lighting, playground for kids, BBQ pits, camp sites, etc. Free car parking and accessible by public transport services...

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Nice little salt water lake catering to fishermen in the middle of the city of Singapore. Well stock local fishes, and many caught their fair share.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Tranquil, leafy and green space that is perfect for outdoor activities and exercises. There is also a pond in the middle of the park and shaded areas for picnics and walks.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Great park, 3.5km along the coastline with easy access from various entry points along Pasir Ris Drive 3.  Great place for walks, yoga, otter watching, bbqs and just enjoying the sea breeze.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Nice place for the exercise and oudoor activities specially for kids. Also can bring your pets. Ideal for Barbecue picnics as there are special setup for that purpose while enjoying the beach and sunset view. But quite far from the central area.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: This is one of the better beachfront parks with a view of Pulau Ubin, lots of fishing spots, mangrove trees and more. I spotted a variety of birds and some others have spotted otters. The running/jogging pathway is always busy in the evening along with cyclists and heavy residents enjoying the cool sea breeze. There’s even a hawker center closeby making it ideal for a break.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Excellent spot for rest n relax.  There are many places to see and if you are a photographer you may get good photos of rare birds.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
403 the lone bus that will bring you here.
Look out for the rooster and hens...they are where you least expect them...so conveniently planted the public toilet...wish there are more shelters for when it rains

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: This park by the beach, enjoy seaview and greenery at the same time. Plenty children playground facility. Great place for everyone!

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: A great place to unwind and exercise. There's a fishing pond for those who are interested to fish. There are audio two small Cafes for some refreshments. You can also chill out with a beer while relaxing.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Weather was a bit stuffy, can't get into the beach water as it was covered seaweeds along the shore. We couldn't find bicycles shops nearby. All we could see was BBQ pit crowded with families & friends. Went into the maize park, it was fun.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Spacious, large playgrounds and nice stretch of beach for strolls and bike rides. Ample parking for drivers. Great place for families

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: 3 gorgeously maintained Parks, each connected by bridges, with foot and bicycle paths and lots of trees for shades. One can get a beautiful sunrise in the morning overlooking the South China Sea. Lots of bbq pits for picnics and overnight camping. Make sure you get a permit if you want to camp overnight. There’s even a horse stable for horseback riding. A wetland where one can see mudskippers and crabs. Monitor lizards, wild chickens, squirrels, otters, hornbills are some of the animals one can look 👀 out for in the Parks.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Definitely a nice place to clock some low mileage about 3-5km in the morning. Worth some cool fresh air!!

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Beautiful place, especially the Boardwalk and the Beach. See a lot of wildlife like Hornbills, Mudskippers, Crabs, etc.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Not too bad, many joggers, cyclists, even people fishing on kayaks. Drop by Kokomo Beach Club for a good kayaking experience

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Big park with many facilities. Biking, running and jogging friendly. The outdoor playground also very nice. There's fishing pond and camp area too.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: A nice park with lot of fishing spots and small playground for kids

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: this is practically my backyard...I've always love running here... there are some construction at a few parts bit it did not impede too much with the running/cycling paths so it was still enjoyable

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
Great place to jog, cycle or just sit down and enjoy the breeze.
You can also catch sights of animals that live by/in the river/canal.
Here’s one for your enjoyment
Adding a photo of the monitor lizard

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: This is beautiful park, it has running track, a restaurant by the beach that also rents out kayaks, SUP and storage for private kayaks and outriggers. You can see keylongs from here in the Singapore strait and ships crossing, it’s beautiful place to spend time anytime of the day. I usually come here to launch my SUP and paddle to Ubin Island on weekends.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Nice place to spend time with family. Best time to go is 6AM or 5PM. Many things to play for children,  can swim at beach.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: This is a great place to be at with a huge fishing pond right in the middle of this sprawling park. Apart from the MRT that is nearby, this is secret nesting place for at least 2 types of herons. Otters frequent the river as do iguanas and terns.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: While cycling to Pasir Ris park, you will pass thru this nice little town park includes a few work out corners and a large fishing pond . Along the canal these buildings caught my eyes with its unique design. Great for family outing.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Service is good. Food out of 10, i would say 6. The meat from the crab breaks apart , very salty and taste is not fresh. The calamari ring was awful. Please don't buy. Veggies tasted burnt. The only food that tasted good is the steam fish.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Lots of green shady trees. Small beach. Watch the boats and ship sail by. Lie on the grass for a lazy day rest. Camp in night. BBQ.   drive you family on quadcycle.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
Lovely park with a nice long kang with a lot of grey herons, monitor lizards, otters and fishes.

You can also spot kingfishers, jungle fowls, parakeets and other wildlife around this town. There is a huge fishing pond as well although I do not advocate that.

There is a hawker Centre in the middle of the park. Overall, a decent place for nature and some food and sights.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Very nice place to bring the little one to play at the few big playgrounds!! With and without sands... and after that we took a stroll by the beach!!

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: lovely place for a stroll. A very old feeling neighborhood park with big fishing pond.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: If you like fishing, you can rent a tent. I don't know about the fishing tools tho. We can see the birds and enjoy the shadowy trees by the river. There's a small playground for your kids. I personally enjoyed my chit chat while walking around the pond or when rested on the bench. And also there's a food court and very nice and clean restroom.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Its clean and safe; police make rounds from time to time.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
Relaxing place.
I visit at least once a month with kids.
Camping is allowed.
Lots of kids play area.
Good for family time.
Enjoy the beach view.
Connected via bus right next to the car park.
Car park D is the first car park.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Love Pasir Ris Park for running, picnic and playgrounds. You can also do kayaking and eat at Georges the Cove with nice seaview. Kids can play on the beach with the sand.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Just a well kept fishing pond, opened for everyone. Nice jogging track around the pond, but have a section under construction

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Nice ambience. Good to organise games for children

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: There are a lot of spots in this park. A big round is around 10k so you can have a 10k jogging area. There are toilets with shower areas every few hundred meters. Some nature walks inside the park itself. A tall above tree height tower. Some areas suitable for family portraits. Tones of playgrounds for children.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Very serene and cool place for a stroll, and the way the park is designed is nice, also there is a hawker if u wanna quick bite. Bridges connecting hdbs to park very delicate. Also good for cycling or jogging, signs are convienient. Overall, very chill feeling and really good for running

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Nice place to do your daily exercises, relax by the beach and also spot some wild sea otters, chicken, eagles, owls…etc.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
It is pretty good, feels like someplace out of a very old movie if you go to the fish pond and watch people fishing. When we were there we saw plenty of success at the ends of the hooks. Good sized fish. It costs money to enjoy the sport but it can be fun.
Other areas include paths and shady walkways. Only thing I did not like was all the smoking. Lots of litter and it did not smell good there.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: It was very nice beach park . I almost slept there in the bench, beautiful air wavin through

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: This park is a short walk from MRT and bus interchange. Plenty of shaded areas, food options, cycle and walking tracks. Great for picnics and family BBQs. There are prawning ponds also if you're into that. And a very hip hawker nearby

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: What a place. Probably the best Nasi Lemak in Singapore. The price, the place and view is unmatched, not to mention the food. Going back again and again.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Great place... Could be better with more shelters by the beach... Cos all the coconut trees are too high up..

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Love the sea facing ; extremely shady huge park with mature trees.. Most welcoming and good to the Halal cafe there.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: A lush and green park with lots of trees providing lots of shade on a hot day. Lots of different playgrounds for kids of all ages and restrooms and wash areas are available for cleaning up after a dip in the sea or washing off the sands from the playgrounds. A great park to bring the kids and family.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Lovely park with a huge playground for the kids, clean beach and lots of nature. We could observe wild owls, birds, otters and many others. Always a great time here!

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Every morning i go for early walk becausei can see beautiful sun rise over there.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Quite a nice place, used to have "fisherman village" leisure and entertainment hub in the past. Now, it has become a wild chickens' place, too many wild chicken running around the park and car park. Don't know where they came from ? The authority need to do something clear away those wild chicken.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: It's a great place to unwind yourself with friends and family. Especially if camping and you are new to it then this is the place. It's just walking distance from Pasir RIS mrt.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Nice little place to visit in the morning when the crowds are thin.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
Nice place to be out in the open.
Went there for a walk.
Spotted otters, wild chickens and a tree with a strange fruit.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Great place for young youths and people for relax and have a bit of outdoors activities. Its around 2.7km long with lots of facility and activities. You can jog, cycle and there is always something for everyone. There are also watersports, horse riding and some pubs around.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Lovely place for a stroll jog or bar b que with friends ! Easier to get the BBQ pits booking compared to ECP . Lot of sheltered places close to the pits for respite from rain . Lots of benches for sitting ! Much less crowded compared to the other beach parks ! Great picnic spots . Few nice restaurants have also come up

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: A quiet beach at dawn where you can marvel at the beauty of sunrise without distraction. It has become one of my favourite place of relaxation and sports for the past 2 years. There are BBQ Pits and tent areas for parties. Usually very crowded on Weekends. There are a few resorts around the beach area too. Great for recreational activities on Weekends and a quiet retreat on weekdays

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Very active park with fishing facilities. Nesrby amenities includs food center  gym, swimming pool.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Other than d best fishing pond this place is quite cool to check out

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Excellent Park. Excited to experience new renovations that are in progress.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Went during evening, quite crowded. But a good place for kids as there are playgrounds for the little ones and the bigger ones.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: This is the fishing pond. Popular place to hang out for anglers and families. Different types of fish ponds to choose. Foods and drinks available. Great place to stroll too. Hawker centre just next to it.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Very beautiful quiet park in pasir ris. It has the beach too . The park is wide spacious for walking cycling and playing . We can also conduct events in large groups .the beach has lot of barbecue pits .order online and enjoy. The beach os also clean and calm. If you around pasir ris its 30 mins walk .take bus 403 which goes to car park F . Never been to the restaurant around . There some pony rides but too expensive . Its faces east u can see only sun rise . Relaxing place overall . The park is also kept clean. I think it further connects to changi beach side.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Peaceful place for a walk and run. The sea and the greenery takes you away from the city stress. Avoid weekends though if u are looking for some peace, as the weekend crowd gives it a family day feel.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Easy parking, good F&B outlets and as it off main stream access, not crowded! :)

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Best place for morning/evening walk. Parking is free for park users. Very less crowded during the week.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: When it comes to BBQ everyone opts for ECP but my choice would be Pasir Ris, the weather fits perfectly here for the BBQ treats with your loved ones. Beach play is better compared to ECP.Camping Sites also available at  few spots n ppl come here for fishing as well..Goody area for Kids,  Not much options for food courts. Go to the nearest car park of your pits otherwise you would end up walking a lot.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
Almost had a near accident with a cyclist. And the cyclist scolded a vulgarity towards me. I don't have eyes behind my head, please!
Pasir Ris Park has 2 pathways and both are shared pedestrians and cyclist.. Why can't pasir ris Park or Nparks make one pathway for cyclist 🚴 and one pathway for pedestrians?

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
My first time BBQ at pasir ris park
Nice location will be back again.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Good place to walk, jog or stroll. You can even get some refreshments or hawker foods after exercising at the sports centre.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Cleanest park i am ever been or seen. Playground are all superbly maintained

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
Was here for BBQ. Blessed that the rain occurs before and after our event. Surprising there is no mosquitoes. (maybe apply too much oil). The pit itself was invaded by ants. They started crawling out after we start the fire.
Will come here again but have to book in advance to secure pits nearer to carpark.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Fantastic! Trip back to nature - mangrove swamp, flying cranes, monitor lizards, spot-tail needlefish, really relaxes your mind. Time stood still for me to appreciate the beauty of the surroundings. And of course the fresh air.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: A good place for morning walk or run.  Big playground for the kids to run around

name: Pasir Ris Town Park

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
It's a nice place to relax near the sea. A few years back, there were just trees, with no other facilities.
Now, there is a play area for kids, cycling tracks.
One can go kayaking as well!
A food shop with choice of foods including vegetarian is available.
There is a good view of the Malaysian coast and nearby islands.
The place is serviced by SBS shuttle bus from Pasir Ris interchange.
We, especially the kids may be tempted to take a dip in the sea water. Yes can, but the water is not very clean. The nearby dry dock adds to the pollution by contributing some dirt with oil!
So a bath in fresh water would be required after a swim/dip in the sea.
During weekends and holidays the place gets crowded.
Overall a good place to visit and relax:-)
Just to add, also be careful when you are in the water. Look out for sharp pebnless, glass pieces and even  sharp sea shells which you hurt your feet.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
Great place to go for families with young kids. There is the space net, long slides, flying fox (two of them), basketball court to kids, playground (for kids who need a bit more help as well), sand pits, and free parking. The public toilets have simple washing up facilities, drinking fountains, and are well maintained all those times I was there. And after a day of play, there is the ever reliable presence of the ice cream uncle/auntie. After a very long day of play, you can get dinner there too.

If you are alright for a walk, cross the bridge at the East end of the park to enter into another section, where there is a huge grassland. Some views of this look as if we were in a farm. Go check out the board walk, where you can see crabs (the kids will like this), and if you are lucky, look out for the hornbills overhead. Latest addition here is a pony ride place.

Certainly a park that is worth returning to.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Good for your basic exercise like jogging and small basic outdoor gym. Pasir Ris sport and recreational center is nearby for your indoor gym and sport courts. Let’s not forget the fishing pond too! Great food sold there.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Nice place with large playgrounds for kids.. YES playgrounds.. with an S.. the place is so huge hundreds of kids can play together. . The bike rental shop is some distance away from the play area. Needs more places to sell drinks though. . Lack of such shops or kiosks..

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Great place for a relaxing outing with family and friends. Big enough to get some exercise as well

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: A simple and chill park to be at for a morning. It is like east coast park but with much lesser crowd.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: So this is quite a decent place for morning jogs and runs or for a matter of fact they can be evenings ones as well. do enojoy your time around here. Parks in Singapore are anyways quite good and well maintained. Do enjoy your visit here.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Great place for family daily  walkabout but  there's a need to monitor E-bike and other form of electronic scooter riding at high speed in the Park . Overall clean and user friendly for BBQ  get together.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Lovely park by Pasir Ris beach, has sufficient restroom facilities and some restaurants in the northern part. Vending machine refilling is matter of luck, still. Best to bring your own beverages.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Relaxing hangouts for family and friends.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: my favourite park in singapore. very beautiful, quiet and underrated. But let's keep it that way, we don't it to be like east coast park, way too crowded.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Quiet, calm , shady park suitable for walking or jogging anytime of the day. The fitness area is also in a shady area. The only drawback is the chin-up bars that are too high to hang or do chin-ups for 5 footers like me. Should be lowered about 12 cm or 5 inches.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
I love this community park in Singapore where the locals bring their pets out for walks. It is a great place to hangout and relax.

The park is very clean, well maintained and has lush healthy trees and grass areas.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Quiet n nice place to exercise or just strolling around. Sometimes you maybe lucky to catch a scene of the pple trying to 'fight' with the fish that caught in the hook. Nice new hawker centre beside.. hopefully we can have more variety of food as quite a number of stalls have closed down recently.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Hands down one of the best parks in Singapore. Spacious & clean, not overly crowded, beautiful beach, huge playground, and even a mangrove boardwalk. Great place to walk around and spend a few hours!

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Breezy, not crowded, even on Sunday evening

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Overall good place for weekend with friend and family. Nice park very spacious to play volleyball, ride bicycle grill your food. No commercial store.  Beach is not for swimming :(. Good amount of street light after sunset. Car parking avaible most of the time and walking distance from Pasir Ris MRT station.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Nice park with good scenery and small wild life, i.e. squirrels, cockerel and hens with chicks, birds...good for bird watching. Also have play ground and open space for all sorts of fitness activities.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Nice park for family gatherings, picnic or barbeque with family and friends. Any office could also have a great bbq get-together here. Many bbq pits available. Need to be booked in advance and kept clean. Games can be played around. A small beach is also there with great sunset views. Been here only once, would love to go there again.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
Fresh air and clean environment.
But unfortunately,  with more campers not enough tiolets. Especially with one under renovation over too long extended period.  The second toilet at that sector often have blockages.  We have been informed the urinals will not be repaired as they will renovate,   in 6 months.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Great massive playground with matured trees providing shade for kids to run around. Beach is right next door with place to wash up available. Felt clean and safe.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Great place for a day of family time. Rest and relax.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
Peaceful quiet park for a stroll!

There are government chalet and the “Downtown East” entertainment center located here.

But personally for myself, the highlight of this park is the swamp area. During the birds migration season (october to march), you will be able to see rare migratory birds here.

oh, did i mention that there are resident spotted wood owls in this park too?

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Great sense of community. Good for cycling, fishing, running etc. Located walking distance from DTE, whitesands, sports hub and pasir ris park so lots to do here

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Pasir Ris Town Park is well equipped with playgrounds for both children and adults. There are jogging and cycling tracks. There is Swamp broadwalk for children and adults to explore . The air is fresh with sea breezes and many greeneries. It is good place to see sunrise and for morning & evening walks. Also suitable for family & friends gatherings and picnics. Its serene environment is very good for unwinding after a day work. There are many wash areas and toilets which are well maintained and cleaned. Ample free public car parks.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Much more quieter and peaceful place than ECP, equally scenic.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Besides enjoying the sea breeze, this park is good for walking and jogging.  Boardwalks built in the mangrove conservation area let you enjoy seeing small water creatures, reptiles and birds.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Beautiful clean park with clean shores, and good community.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Greenery with calmly sea beach make the place heavenly...

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Tranquil and relaxing park for walks, biking  and photography. For those whom nature is close to their heart - watch grey herons, kingfishers and sea eagles stalk and catch fish. Several grey herons have made their nests up in the highest trees by the river. One of the best parks to take your family to and to be close to nature !

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
one of the best park in the east, lots of greenery and space to enjoy your outdoor activities.
it a place for everyone, with friend, family or by yourself.
Come and experience.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Must visit Park area in Singapore. The park is divided into 3 sections. Park A,B,C respectively. All sections are health centric by default. Park A is mostly breeze full and you can lookout lot of families enjoying, partying out. Park B is short distant in Sea front but little elongated in depth from sea sore. Park C is where kids play area is available.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: A 3km park with nice beach views and plenty of toilets around. You can try out water activities at the nearby water venture or have a nice walk or cycle here. Good for those who want to take a break from work and destress. You can also use this park to travel to Punggol which is nice.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Car park E,  which have more play area for kids,  very relaxing and entertaining place for both parents and kids. Very lovely environment easily accessible to the busstand and call taxi. Beach was nice, but sometimes if we stand in water we can feel that some crabs byte your legs. The rest nice to visit the place with the family to spend time with relax on weekends in Singapore.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Happy and fun day with the family! weather is good, cloudy and windy though a little drizzling.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Finally see clean beach at Pasir Ris! 🌴⛱️🌊🏖️

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Had BBQ, place is good

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Nice and breezy place to relax ....

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Walks in the park in the morning is cool and you get a chance to see the sun rising. Park users are friendly too. It always puts a smile on my face. Good way to start a day.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Good place to chill and fish..the fish can be quite lazy, so don't expect a big fish. Management also needs to actively lookout for guys trying to scoop fish up with their nets rather than fishing.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Wonder nature in the midst of HDB blocks. Parents may go fishing while children go for music lessons in a nearby Music Dreamz School - the top choice music school for specialised keyboard courses for children - Fun With Keyboard Course. Don't miss out the free trial where you can find out more details. Let children become musicians today! Who knows they can be future pro! 😊

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
Ok.
More fun for upper primary kids where they can climb and then slide down. But after few hrs when the rain has stopped, most of the slides can't be play as most of the slides had pool of rain water at the bottom of the slides.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: It was just amazing place

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Awesome place. Clean. Head down towards the fishing pond area to do some fishing and prawning. A few cool bars are around as well for quick bites and drinks. Cool place in the middle of pasir ris to chill and relax

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Had to go here with several classmates. Quite intriguing, especially the mangrove areas, and there were even some chickens running about in the park and a lot of crabs(coastal mangrove area)! I highly recommend this place to people who just want to cycle and relax, or even bring their family out! The scenery and animals never fails to impress me.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Perfect place to do BBQ

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: It's kinda sad given that they are slowly treating this place apart.  The structures aren't as stable anymore and the climbing net is so shaky, I had to get off for my own safety.  The climbing bridge is also gone.  I hope the authorities could give this place the maintenance it needs and rebuilt it to it's former glory.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Amazing place with a hidden treasure- Mangrove Boardwalk, and definitely a haven for children with the wide array of fun activities and play equipment at the playground! The iconic spiderweb has been there for the longest time! Love the play area- for kids 5-12 yo! So if you are not within this range, please refrain from using the play equipment so that they can last for several generations.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
It's about 3.9km end to end along the beach.
It's divided into 4 areas that have 65 BBQ pits along the entire stretch of the park. Camping is only permitted in area 1 n 3 only.
Area 3 have more children friendly playground n playthings.
Free Carpark available at Carpark D n F only, others are pay to park.
A very good area to jog, walk, cycle n relax.
Not suitable for swimming though bcos beach is rather dirty n murky and with green algae n seaweed. Adequate toilet facilities like shower and water cooler available every 200 to 300 metres apart. Drinks dispenser machines are located within the toilets facilities. Good camping area but you require a camping permit that can be applied through AXS machines. Camping is allowed
in areas 1 n 3 only.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Good place for a short getaway!

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
Nice park with a jogging / walking /cycling track around it. Shady with lots of tree cover too. It is next to a river where if lucky, you can spot an otter family.
There's a commercially run fishing pond. It used to smell badly but the management has made efforts to oxygenate the water vigorously with water wheels. The pond doesn't emit that smell anymore.
There's a car park attached and also nearby HDB car parks. It is a one-minute walk from Pasir Ris Interchange and MRT station. The Pair Ris Sports Centre and the new food centre is just next to it. A very convenient location.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Green around, with a fishing pond in centre. Have jogging path, hawker centre, gymnasium, swimming pool all nearby. Walking distance from Pasir ris mrt.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Fun is all that matters. And there is an ice cream 🍦 truck on the road side.🤣🤣💙💙💙💙

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
An impressive park. Massive old trees and grassy spaces opening to a shoreline. Hidden mangrove boardwalk and tower, bike paths and benches to just sit and watch the sea. Joggers in the morning shared it with folks doing their morning tai chi.

Gets warm quickly and unfortunately shops for drinks were a bit thin on the ground. Great place to send s few hours before the heat of the day. Might be a few mozzies but that's par for the course in this climate.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: A nice view of the beach, very easily accessible with the Bus Interchange and the MRT(Subway/Metro) Station is nearby. There are also shopping malls nearby with plenty of places to eat at. Nice for a jog or cycle

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: It's a lovely place. Nice park to walk abt n exercise. Hawker ctr n mall near by. Food n drink stalls at ur convenience. We went fishing at pasir pond today 7am to 4pm. We caught only 3 fish (1 seabass 1 snapper 1 mangrove jack) our friends caught a lot more.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: This part of the park has a nice stocked pond for fishing if that's something you're interested in. Easy to get to from the MRT and there are LOTS of spots to cast your rod.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
There is a crocodile at pasir ris park
Do not swim over there

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Big salt-water fishing pond with sea bass, grouper, promfet, snapper and Magrove Jack.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Footpath leveled higher to minimize flooding.  Better greenery. But, certain parts nearer to pasir ris drive 1 has been closed to pedestrians for construction of new MRT line

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Great place to exercise in the morning.Very cooling but there's a pond where people do fishing/prawning so there is a fishy smell sometimes. But still a great place to exercise.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Campsite 3 bbq pit number 37.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
The one and only pond...oohh well,what can we say....
Fish ON!!.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: One of the nice park for local neighborhood or visitors. It has a fishing pond, cycling path and jogging path for day . At night, it has choices of restaurants and cafes for dinner and good place to chill with your friends.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Food court with nice food

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Pasir ris town park is an excellent place to visit with family and friends. There is a huge variety of activites you could do there. I could name a few such as: go on walks, play at the beach or in the water, play at the playground or go for a barbeque. The park is quite big and it usually not crowded. It is also generally quite clean. For those wondering, there are toilets and parking lots in the area. This place is also wheelchair accessible with lifts and ramps to accommodate wheelchairs.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Near white sand shopping centre and MRT .fishing pond and food courts and path for jogging plus Down town east .

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Pasir Ris Park 3 has become my training ground for hammock camping.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: It is a big place and has an excellent playground for children. Also many accessible toilet facilities for washing up.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Here's a very tranqull & very peaceful place. Very good for outdoor activity and exercise, The only bad thing is it's very far deep into the jungle area. Need to have transport in order to go into this place.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Having my afternoon snack 云吞面 here, price are cheap ,coffee without sugar just 60 cents a cup

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Great place for urban anglers but I’m not a fan of fishing. Take that out of the equation and it’s a pretty ordinary park. Check out the yacht though.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Was there on a gloomy Saturday morning for cleaning up of the beach. Luckily it was not raining cats and dogs just little drizzle.  Like all beaches. It is serene and chilling for an exercise at the park. Of course.. bbq should be inclusive. =)

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
Interesting park as you can see storks perching on the canal railings. Sometimes, there are big monitor lizards swimming across the canals. The park also has a fishing pond in the middle. It seems to be quite crowded, especially on weekends.
Sometimes, you see show-offs and inconsiderate people doing yoga IN THE MIDDLE of the walking paths, so other passers-by got to walk on the grass!!Shouldn't it be the other way?? If you want to show off your latest yoga poses, do it on the grass area, not park yourself in the middle of the walking path and expect others to walk around you!!No freaking common sense and social manners!!
Now that the food centre at the edge of this park is open, there will definitely be more park-goers. Across this park is the relatively newly renovated White Sands mall where the Pasir Ris MRT station is situated as well.
A decent selection of retail and food shops and stores.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
Quite an okay jogging route. Flat ground most of the way and it is also not very crowded during the evening hours.

The Pasir Ris Hawker Centre is just beside the park also so it's extremely covenient to have your meal right after jogging.

There is also a small fishing pond.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Great for picnic and kids! Nice toilet facilities available nearby. Restaurants near the park as well. Come in the early evening. Play at the park and end with a nice dinner at the restaurants!

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Almost 4km of beachfront with mangrove boardwalk along river. F&B outlets and surfboards rental.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Good place for walk, jogging, nature trails, beach walk with lots of greenery and old trees. Few restaurant for food snacks and drinks. Some playground for kids fun activity.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Very relaxing, you can participate in fishing,prawning or just stroll around the huge lake :) i'd recommend the restaurant Wok This Way as the service and food are extremely good!

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Nice but unnecessarily the Social distancing people harassing often even we just in group of 4 eating on picnic. It's kind of threat the last guy gave, the way they talk is too rude and seems they are in too much of power!

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: great park with 3 full restaurants and one lite eating place, 2 paddleboard/kayak rental, multiple restrooms, etc. really nice

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Great walkways...quiet and out of the way

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: One place next to the sea and have a good walk in nature. We came here last time to roller blade once, fell because some parts are not paved properly. But they seemed to have fixed it all up.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Great place for cycling, walking, paddling.  Can use park network connectivity to get to Gardens by the Bay. Not too many places to eat.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: One can spot 🐓s  and even 🦉. Nice relaxing park with playground that children would love. Parking is complimentary too.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Serenity and tranquility are what you can find in this park. The park is also near the beach, people love to take a stroll, go jogging, or walk their dog here.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Always a favourite of kids for the playground, slides and swings....

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: A very well equipped park for the children as well as adults to spend quality time with friends and family.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Everything you deserve at beach is here

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Wonderful park next to MRT in pasir ris...few food joints and bars to spend quite and nice evenings...the pond in the park if full of anglers whole night!

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Fun place to be with your family. You could pitch a tent and use a small barbecue set to heat up and let the kids play at the playground which has a lot of items to play with.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Nice and peaceful place for cycling. There are chickens, crabs, herons, hornbills, monitor lizards, mudskippers, otters, ponies and even boars if you are lucky.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Not worth going if you're not a fan of fishing and the smell of fish pond. It's surrounded by tall buildings, so don't expect any breeze. Just warm humid stale air.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Nice town park with a fishing pond and a hawker centre. Along the canal or river... there are also several kind of wild reptiles and migratory birds.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: A very convenient place to be especially if you are living in pasir ris as there are a lot of sports facilities and there is a huge park to cycle or jog . The MRT , the sports center , the park and the shopping mall are all walking distance .

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Great place to enjoy sunset and cycling and strolling and destress.quite windy in the evening on certain months. Somemore it's also near to Pasir ris MRT station. Great place for me with my kid to enjoy the beauty of nature in this country.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Nice beach. Barbeque pits available.  But need to book early. Kids play area is nice but evening times over crowded .. cos of so many kids gathering here

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: With the new social enterprise, Fairground multi storey hawker centre... proximity to the MRT station..has a fun n relaxing ground for young n seniors. Coffee  O @$0.70 cent per cuppa is a rare treat. Western grille $5.90 + $1/- soup of the day completes your day. Many more treats awaits your support.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Great place newly taken over by a new company.Great leisure fishing not only for adults but kids too.Nice place for seafood and drinks.Bestvtime early morning for fishing and late evenings.Food open after 4 pm..

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
Very silly way to place barbecue pits.
All pits were on a grass patch.
It was raining the day before we went there.
And the grass had puddles of water and was muddy.
No choice but to step on the grass to go to our pit as there are no walkways !!!
Sembawang park is way better!

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Near to White Sands mall and the Pasir Ris MRT & Bus Interchange. Popular with anglers who come for a catch at the fishing pond (need to pay, of course). Fishing and prawning available here, thus an avenue for family activities. Has food options like a pub within the park itself, or the Pasir Ris food centre with the usual hawker food fare at level 1 and more bespoke dishes on level 2.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Really nice place to chill. Great atmosphere and good food options. Optimal place to bring kids over to cycle or just run around. There's even a fishing pond.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Very nice place to go for a morning/evenjng walk/jog. Good place for children too. Lot of play areas and fun for children to try. Public Transport also available from Pasir Ris Station. Bus 403. Frequency is every 10-12 mins.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Best place for weekend handout for both adults and kids. This place has wide varieties of play areas for kids and adults. It has barbeque pits and wine and dines nearby car park D

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: One of my favourite parks. Nice quiet place to chill out and go for walks.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Cool breeze, nice view of the fishery activities,  can see big vessel parked nearby. The water must be "supoosingly" clean because I see one otter's family hunting in the water.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Get here at dawn to see the changing purple pink hues of the sky as they change to blue and orange as the sun rises. If you turn right after entering the park from the carpark, it's a  doable 2km well-paved route to the end, great for walking in groups or on your own. There are many joggers in the morning and a taichi group to accompany you in your exercise!

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Serene and peaceful at night.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Nice and serene place, and quite convenient to get to. But nowhere to hide when it rains! Only visit during good weather.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Clean air, nice view

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Excellent park with great views. Would recommend cycling here while enjoying the sea view and try out the huge playground. Nice place to relax and it's not too crowded.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: To be honest.  Chili's crab was a let down.  Not worth the money. We also order the hot plate tofu and it's missing the most important part of the dish. A layer of egg. We had fried sambal kangkong. It was terrible. Overall the dishes there are total rubbish. Will not visit it again.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Underappreciated town park with actually very close access to a mangrove, Downtown East. It's right beside the Pasir Ris MRT, Eastpoint Mall, a hawker centre, swimming pool, mcdonalds, burger king. Really awesome.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Peaceful and have a lot of land to do a run/walk. Also there's the coastal feel so makes this place very different in feel. Do bring mozzie spray as there can be some.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Relix fishing 🎣

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: One of the better park in Singapore

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Fantastic place to stay very open n serene not congested

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Lovely park ...great location...clean n has a shop to buy stuff you forgot to bring ect...but the loos were few and far in between...n  very dirty ....can get crowded on weekends n public holidays...the narrow beach was pretty dirty too ....saw n heard lots of beautiful n rare birds....well lit

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: This is the park with sea nearest to my place. Well bring family there at least once a month. Feel there sea breeze and enjoy the sand & water.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: This is a nice plc for cycling, camping and jogging. Jogging track is 7km. Camping with permit is safe.. a public bus 403 brings you in here from pasir ris interchange.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Clean Cool Place To Chill In This Urban Jungle.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Pasir Ris Park is really unassuming. Don't expect fancy botany and thrills. Come here for the sea, some green, and chillax atmosphere of Pasir Ris. It ain't lepak town for no reason. I recommend taking a walk through the mangrove trail. Otherwise it's a great family outing place. Book barbeque pits, tenting spots, or hang out at the playgrounds.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Great playground for children however if u swim at the beach take note there is no shower facilities

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Walked the mangrove park. Nice walk. Not too much of mosquitoes and close enough to see some nature animals and plants. Simple walk even for the kiddos

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: A beautiful, serene and tranquil park. Love going to this place for walk. One of the least crowded parks in Singapore reason maybe that it's not much commercialized, one has to walk to downtown east for his/her kopi fix. I like it this way though. This is the only park in Singapore where you can find some form of wildlife other than the monkeys. I have personally seen Python, a black colour snake, Otters, Wild Boars, monitor lizards(if you are lucky you might find these lizards wrestling) and long of list of birds from Chickens to Herons. A fantastic energizer to kick start your day or great stress buster after a long day at work. Did I forget to mention  about the water sports and bars towards the Elias side of the park ? Yes you can get high on booze or adrenaline.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: A good place for sunset viewing

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: If you find White Sands Mall rather over crowded, walk across the road toward Pasir Ris Town Park and you will find this wonderful food court with endless of selections of local delights that won't break your wallet! Connected to the sport hall this place serve various food on the 1st & 2nd floor. Oh, you can also serve the internet for free!

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Another place that you can bring your Beloved Pet dog for Walks or for Family outing for Fresh Air as A Family in One Spirit and One Mind two by two.👬👭👫

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: One of the most visited Outstanding place for traveler, family, friends and couple. See the view of sunset on dancing water. The place has so many facilities. Spend a very quality time here.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Beautiful park..close to sea, rustic environent and boardwalk within the mangroves.  My dog loves exploring the boardwalk.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Tranquil, greenery, great nature lovers

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Spacious outdoor area with lots of play activities scattered around to accommodate many kids. Plenty of places with shades for family to rest while keeping an eye on their kids.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: There is abundant greenery, and the boardwalk amongst the mangroves is interesting. It's easy to spot monitor lizards, crabs, hornbills, herons and other birds.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text:
Very calm cool place to feel freedom.

name: Pasir Ris Town Park
review_text: Presently the boardwalk is under renovation. Will reopen on the 20th April. But the number of mangroves trees are flourishing with the constant care by the NP staff. The numerous adaptations of the species in the different zonation where there are eg pencil roots of the Avacinea, Brugiera n Sonneriatia are there for you to identify. Also there's the nursery where most of the mangrove propugules are nurse for replanting. l saw a laced woodpecker, Sunbirds, bulbuls n a snake. Another interesting feature is the kitchen garden, where herbs and spices can be found. As for the kids a butterfly garden n a maze would make it very interesting place to visit.
